HEADWORD: Kami
<hw>Ka"mi</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[Japanese,
<tr>god</tr>.]</ety> <def>A title given to the celestial gods of the
first mythical dynasty of Japan and extended to the demigods of the
second dynasty, and then to the long line of spiritual princes still
represented by the mikado.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Kamichi</ent>⟦br⟧
